<div id="outline-container-purpose-of-the-project" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="purpose-of-the-project"><a id="sec-1-2" name="sec-1-2"></a><span class="section-number-3">1.2</span> Purpose of the project</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-purpose-of-the-project">

<p>
Explore ways of using plain text for personal organising, managing
information, and communicating - then writing a simple guide or set of
how-to notes.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-overview-of-plain-text" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="overview-of-plain-text"><a id="sec-1-3" name="sec-1-3"></a><span class="section-number-3">1.3</span> Overview of plain text</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-overview-of-plain-text">

<p>
Write a section drawing on:
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="http://plaintext-productivity.net/">Introduction | Plaintext
Productivity</a> todo.txt, notes and organising. How to use with
Windows.
</li>
<li><a href="http://blog.scottlowe.org/2015/04/06/plain-text-productivity-experiment/">The
Plain Text Productivity Experiment · Scott's Weblog</a>
</li>
<li><a href="https://zapier.com/blog/plain-text-files-for-productivity/">10
Plain Text Files You Should Have on Your Desktop for Higher
Productivity</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

